<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/835</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of the
                                American Republics</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Duggan</hi>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-20">July 20, 1937</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Mr. Huneeus of the Chilean Embassy telephoned to say that the Ambassador,
                            who is out of town, just received an instruction from the Foreign Office
                            stating that the Chilean representative at the Chaco Peace Conference
                            has been instructed to work in “full agreement” with the representative
                            of the United States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Laurence Duggan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>